---

## CRITICAL architecture fix: disable stem looping

The current AudioEngine sets `src.loop = true` on every stem. With real MP3s of varying lengths, looping will cause desync. **Set `src.loop = false` in `_createSources`**. The transport stops at `totalDuration` via the RAF loop; stems that end early (guide, click) just go silent naturally — no desync.

Change `_createSources` line ~329:
```js
src.loop = false;  // was: true
// remove src.loopStart / src.loopEnd lines entirely
```

Also: `seek()` re-creates sources from an offset. With non-looping real files, `src.start(t, offset)` still works correctly — Web Audio plays from the given offset to the end.

