## Mixer.jsx change (Step 4)

Mixer currently `import { STEM_CONFIG } from '../data/songs.js'` and maps over it.

**App.jsx**: Add `song={song}` to `<Mixer>` props (already has stemState, onVolume, onMute, onSolo, onPan).

**Mixer.jsx**: Replace STEM_CONFIG usage:
```jsx
// Remove: import { STEM_CONFIG } from '../data/songs.js';
// Add song to destructured props:
export default function Mixer({ song, stemState, onVolume, onMute, onSolo, onPan }) {
  if (!stemState || !song || Object.keys(stemState).length === 0) { ... }
  return (
    <div className="mixer">
      {song.stems.map(config => {
        const stem = stemState[config.id];
        if (!stem) return null;
        return <ChannelStrip key={config.id} config={config} stem={stem} ... />;
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

## Lazy loading note

Add `abortController` support to `loadSong` so switching songs mid-load cancels the in-flight fetches. Simple pattern: store `this._loadAC = new AbortController()` at start of loadSong, pass `{ signal: this._loadAC.signal }` to each `fetch()`, and call `this._loadAC.abort()` at the top of the next `loadSong` call. Prevents 200MB of concurrent fetches if user clicks between songs quickly.

